title: Operation: Outer Space
creator: Murray Leinster
description: LibriVox recording of Operation: Outer Space, by Murray Leinster. Read by Mark Nelson. Jed Cochrane is about to take off on man's first interstellar voyage. His mission: Make sure it's good television! (Introduction by Mark Nelson) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; adventure; fantasy; fiction; science fiction
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text

reviews.reviewbody:
I only made it through the entire story because it was short and it was being read by Mark N; normally stories this boring I stop listening to.

The story tries to be a sci-fi, but there is really no adventure, no grand discoveries, nothing.  It just never takes off.  The crew goes on some flights and argues with earth over tv rights.  It just doesn't move, IMHO.

Mark Nelson is a great reader, so you might like the story better than I did.
